    "description": "<p>You are an ever present source of aid for your allies. You gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Ranged Help Attack: </strong>When you take the <strong>Help</strong> <strong>Action</strong> to aid an <strong>Attack</strong>, you can be within <strong>10 Spaces</strong> of the Attacker or the target of the Attack (instead of 1 Space).</p></li><li><p><strong>Help Reaction:</strong> When a creature that you can see within <strong>10 Spaces</strong> makes an <strong>Attack</strong>, a <strong>Skill Check,</strong> or a <strong>Trade</strong> <strong>Check</strong>, you can spend <strong>1 AP</strong> as a <strong>Reaction</strong> to grant them a <strong>Help Die</strong> that it can use on that <strong>Check</strong>.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Help Enhancements</span></strong></p><p>When you grant a creature a <strong>Help</strong> <strong>Die</strong>, you can spend <strong>MP</strong> to grant the target additional aid. </p><p>The target gains 1 of the following enhancements per <strong>MP</strong> spent. You canâ€™t choose the same Enhancement more than once.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Lasting Help:</strong> The Help Die now lasts up to 10 minutes, and is considered a <strong>Lasting</strong> <strong>Help</strong> <strong>Die</strong>. A creature can only have 1 Lasting Help Die at a time.</p></li><li><p><strong>Save Help:</strong> Your Help Die can be used on a Save the target makes.</p></li><li><p><strong>Healing Help:</strong> The target immediately regains <strong>2 HP</strong> or gains <strong>2 Temp HP</strong> (your choice).</p></li><li><p><strong>Damaging Help:</strong> If the <strong>Help</strong> <strong>Die</strong> is used as part of an Attack, the damage increases by 3 against a target of your choice.</p></li></ul>",
